The paper discusses state-of-the-art recommendation algorithms and proposes a knowledge base representation learning approach for personalized recommendation. This work involves the integration of structured and unstructured data, which is a common theme in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The use of knowledge bases and embeddings is also a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database (cs.DB) research. Finally, the paper discusses the use of textual reviews, which is a common theme in natural language processing (cs.CL) research.
